OL,3,CInterest rates held at 5.25% - what is
OL,4,Cthe bank waiting for?
OL,6,FThe Bank of England now forecasts that
OL,7,Fthe headline annual rate of inflation
OL,8,Fwill be back at the target rate 2% by
OL,9,FMay, a year and a half sooner than it
OL,10,Fwas expecting just three months ago.
OL,12,FThe market price of oil and gas has
OL,13,Ffallen significantly since November,
OL,14,Finflation is fading fast.
OL,16,FThere's strong possibility that the UK
OL,17,Feconomy entered a technical recession
OL,18,Fat the end of 2023 (probability: a
OL,19,Fcoin's toss) and growth this year and
OL,20,Fnext is forecast to be dismal.
