OL,3,CInterest rates held at 5.25% - what is
OL,4,Cthe bank waiting for?
OL,6,FThe language has changed. At least the
OL,7,Fprospect of interest rate cuts is now
OL,8,Fbeing acknowledged.
OL,10,FThe clear message appears to be that
OL,11,Frates have probably peaked, that the
OL,12,Fnext move will be down - it's just a
OL,13,Fquestion of when.
OL,15,FOne member of the Monetary Policy
OL,16,FCommittee, Swati Dhingra, voted for an
OL,17,Fimmediate cut. But two, Jonathan
OL,18,FHaskel and Catherine Mann, wanted
OL,19,Fanother increase.
