OL,3,CInterest rates held at 5.25% - what is
OL,4,Cthe bank waiting for?
OL,6,FThe Bank's concern is that although
OL,7,Finflation is likely to return to 2% in
OL,8,Fthe summer, it's unlikely to stay
OL,9,Fthere. From July, the Bank thinks
OL,10,Finflation will be rising again,
OL,11,Fnearing 3% in March 2025.
OL,13,FThe economic shocks which propelled
OL,14,Fprices upwards - the pandemic and
OL,15,FRussia's invasion of Ukraine - have
OL,16,Feased but the evidence suggests
OL,17,Finflation continues to feed itself
OL,18,Fdomestically.
